1 (5) An assessment imposed by a special district, special improvement district, or rural
2 improvement district that is created through a petition by owners within a proposed district is presumed to be a
3 special assessment unless a property owner establishes that the requirements of this section are not satisfied.
4 (6) Nothing in this section confers rights on a local government to impose an assessment, and any
5 assessment imposed must comply with the applicable legal requirements for imposition of the assessment.
6 (7) For the purposes this section, the term "assessment" means any charge or assessment on
7 property by a local government, except property taxes authorized by Title 15 and Title 20 and fees for services
8 provided for in 7-6-4013.
